caption: Amazing dish at friendly price. I'm from Taiwan and sometimes I would crave for my hometown food. Then I would go there and get their sausage fried rice and basil bean curd. Their popcorn chicken is very well marinated, and their staffs are super kind. Their taro tapioca is the best in the states. Their milk foam tea is great too (similar to gong cha, and I sometimes prefer Dolphin Bay's for the simplicity) I sometimes get their beef noodle soup and spicy dumpling (紅油抄手). Make sure you get a stamp card to collet stamps for free drink and minced pork rice.
This place is the best around! Great service and the best Taiwanese food around! Its almost like a home cooked meal.
Amazing food and service!! Popcorn chicken, beef stuffed pancakes, boiled vegetables, and small pork rice were all so good!! Very very reasonable prices as well
Food was incredible as was the service! Super friendly and nice staff. Chicken was nice and crispy and tea was refreshing and sweet.
Nice spot for lunch or takeout, visited many times, not once disappointed. If you want a quick, satisfying meal, come here

Great food and service! I’ve been here a few times over the last few years and the food always delivers. I hadn’t been here in a while but I today I made the 3 mile trek there through a snow storm and it was well worth it. The owner threw in a tea on the house which made my day! Thanks dolphin bay! I’ll be back soon :)
Very good Taiwanese cuisine and tasted like home.

Having lived in Boston for the past 5 years, I have tried several different Taiwanese restaurants and this is definitely the best I have ever tasted. It feels like home because of the pleasant service they provide. Also, fun fact, it is owned by a cute Taiwanese family! Dolphin Bay was also started in California and they moved all the way to the east coast!! So lucky to have the opportunity to taste food just like what I tasted at home! Brings back my memories :)
Delicious food and very friendly and accommodating staff!
It is the best place to eat traditional Taiwanese food, the drinks, the service and the food are the best.
Really great popcorn chicken. Will absolutely go here again.

Fantastic comfort food I would order regularly if I lived in the area! Service for takeout was excellent as well. Would highly recommend the da bing egg pancake (my favorite) as well as the spicy popcorn chicken and spicy wontons.
Favorite taiwanese restaurant!  Affordable, large servings and delicious!
The popcorn chicken I ordered was overcooked and burnt! Can’t believe that the restaurant felt comfortable with serving the burnt food. Very disappointed with the food quality.

Food was good.  My wife is Taiwanese and this is closest to Taiwan we have found in Boston.  Less oil, less salt like Taiwan food has. Beef Noodle soup was good but noodles were a little soft.  Service was fine. This is a small place for college students so don't expect a fine luxury dining experience. It's a small casual place.
Interesting place for shared living

Small location but great food! I had a friend order for me and all the food was amazing. The curry, whiterice and pork and fermented beans dish was amazing! The curry was not spicy like Indian curry and had a great flavor. The service was very quick. I highly recommend the brown sugar boba tea!!
Good food, good place, and good service. Really like this place and will visit again if I'm ever in Boston

Gods I don't know how I go every few weeks without this place.   I order food from here on Postmates.  It arrives very quickly and their Pork Belly rice is one of the most delicious and comforting pork dishes.   The braised pork belly is super soft and melts in your mouth.  They also have amazing popcorn chicken!
Very great and authentic Taiwan food!
Loved the beef noodle soup and shrimp fried rice! Staff are super friendly!!
Authentic Taiwanese food. Best service in town. I'll definitely return to try more dishes.

We came back and got a 刨冰 (shaved ice) and a 牛肉捲餅 (beef roll).  牛肉捲餅 combines a 蔥油餅 (green onion pancake) and braised beef. Dolphin Bay's 蔥油餅 is wonderfully fragrant, redolent of fresh onion and yeasty dough. It manages to be  both crisp and chewy, with many thin layers, without being greasy. A lot of places have very dry, tough, beef, but Dolphin Bay uses braised beef shank, which is tender and slimy and melts in your mouth. The only flaw to this dish is that the there's a bit too much sauce, making the whole thing slightly too salty.  We ordered 刨冰 with slices of sweetened taro, red bean, boba, and egg pudding. The ice itself was sweetened with condensed milk, and the whole thing was cool, lightly sweet, and refreshing. The order was a bit too big for the two of us to finish, but it was so good that we took some of the liquid home in a cup for later.  The staff were very accommodating of our 1 year old, even when he escaped and started crawling across the restaurant.
Excellent food, friendly service.

The food is reasonably priced and delicious.  I had the salt and pepper porkchop. It was perfectly cooked and seasoned.  The porkchop was served over white rice, had brocolli as the vegetable, and a cubed potatoes, carrots, and tofu in a spicy sauce.  Will definitely return to this restaurant.

Great Taiwanese restaurant for students because of how affordable it is. Its main audience is college students but families are welcome as well.  I really like their noodle soups. They make for a hearty meal. Also very clean bathrooms. They are also known for their boba tea. Their staff make the best boba tea and you can specify how much sugar you want (ex. Half sugar or little sugar or no sugar, which is what I go for). Their boba pearls are also meticulously prepared so that it is always the perfect texture of chewy throughout the entire ball.

By far the best Taiwanese restaurant in Boston. Dolphin Bay features a wide range of classic Taiwanese cuisines with most of them tasting absolutely amazing. Shrimp Fried Rice, Jalapeno Gravy on Rice, Pork Chop on Rice and Dolphin Bay Slush are my favorites. In addition to great food, Dolphin Bay also features great services. The servers are genuinely friendly and passionate about what they're doing. I've had some really pleasant conversations with them
